		<body>
			<pb n="1"/>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Richmond</placeName> <date>June 14.1849</date></p>
				<p>Valued Friend</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">I perceived in the last no of<lb/> the &#8220;Occident&#8221; an article written by<lb/> <persName>Mr Brown</persName> relative to the <date>Sunday</date><lb/> Laws of <placeName>Pennsylvania</placeName>&#44; and I regret<lb/> much that every effort has been in<lb/> vain to modify that obnoxious Law<lb/> in your state&#44; a session before the<lb/> last of our Legislature when they revis&#45;<lb/>ed our Criminal Laws I had the<lb/> matter under consideration in the<lb/> Senate nearly two days relative to<lb/> the <date>Sabbath</date> Laws here in which<lb/> <persName>Mr <sic>Stanard</sic></persName> and others took a very<lb/> active part.  I think that I sent you<lb/> the papers containing the remarks<lb/> on the subject&#44; they were however only<lb/> slightly modified and that only by<lb/> the casting vote of the speaker&#44; the law<lb/> as reported by the revisers read thus<lb/> &#8220;If any person on <date>Sabbath</date> day shall<lb/> himself be found labouring &#38;c &#38;c&#8221; and<lb/> the amendment asked for in the Senate<lb/> was a proviso for persons who had<lb/> kept the <date>Sabbath</date> day of the congregation<lb/> to which they may have belonged to be<lb/> exempt from the penalty of the law</p>
			<pb n="2"/>
				<p>which was lost by a vote of 20 to 5<lb/> the amendment was then asked for to<lb/> insert the word &#8220;a&#8221; so as to read &#8220;If any<lb/> person on <hi rend="underline">a</hi> <date>sabbath</date> day &#8220;&#38;c &#38;c&#8221; and in order<lb/> to get that slight amendment it was<lb/> a tie vote the speaker giving the casting<lb/> vote.  You will perceive that the<lb/> law as reported was done to recognize<lb/> a <date>Sabbath</date> day and not to leave it dis&#45;<lb/>cretionary with the magistrate to say<lb/> which was the <date>sabbath</date> day&#44; the title<lb/> of the Chapter in which this law may<lb/> be found in Chap VIII &#8220;Of <sic>offences</sic><lb/> against Chastity Morality and Decency&#8221;<lb/> Revised Code <date>1848</date> page III.  <persName>Mr Mays</persName><lb/> and <persName>Standard</persName> told me then that if<lb/> we had have had any &#39;<sic>competant</sic><lb/> person to have argued the point before<lb/> the committee we would have had<lb/> matters fixed our own way&#44; but in<lb/> this particular we were minus.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">We have now an extra session<lb/> of the Legislature for the purpose of<lb/> revising the Civil Code and I believe<lb/> the Criminal also.  I regret that they<lb/> have adjourned from here to the<lb/> springs.  I did intend to use my eff<lb/>orts to get this matter set right in</p>
			<pb n="3"/>
				<p>regard to that law&#44; I <sic>seen</sic> <persName>Mr Standard</persName><lb/> to day and I had a long talk with<lb/> him on the subject and presented him<lb/> with a copy of the last &#39;Occident&#8221; he<lb/> assures me that he will use his efforts<lb/> to have it modified.  I am sure were<lb/> you here and present at the legislature<lb/> you could urge our claims in such lan<lb/>guage before the committees that could<lb/> not be easily mis&#45;understood&#44; would to<lb/> God I had the ability I would do<lb/> my utmost to have things right&#44; as they<lb/> ought to be I feel a great interest in<lb/> the matter and have enlisted many of<lb/> <sic>of</sic> the members of the Legislature from<lb/> time to time in our favour&#44; I wish<lb/> you would write an article relative<lb/> to the matter&#44; and if to the purpose<lb/> I am sure it will have the desired<lb/> effect I will have it published and<lb/> well distributed among the members&#44;<lb/> you know that the petition you wrote<lb/> for me to the common Hall of this city<lb/> was the means of the repeal of the<lb/> <date>Sabbath</date> law of <placeName>Richmond</placeName>&#44; and I am<lb/> sure with a little work we can accomplish<lb/> our end.  Truly yours.  <hi rend="underline"><persName role="author">Jacob Ezekiel</persName></hi></p>
				<p>Love to sister and all relatives</p>
			<pb n="4"/>
				<p><addressee>Rev. Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
